/ This example shows use of submodules to give information / / about the chip, board and overall device. / / / / The main attestation is associated with the chip with the / / CPU and running the main OS. It is what has the keys and / / produces the token. / / / / The board is made by a different vendor than the chip. / / Perhaps it is some generic IoT board. / / / / The device is some specific appliance that is made by a / / different vendor than either the chip or the board. / / / / Here the board and device submodules aren't the typical / / target environments as described by the RATS architecture / / document, but they are a valid use of submodules. /
